<h1>Privacy Policy for SEB Config Verificator</h1>
<p><strong>Last Updated:</strong> [Insert Date]</p>

<p>
This Privacy Policy describes how the <strong>SEB Config Verificator</strong> Chrome Extension ("the Extension") 
collects, accesses, uses, and protects information when used in authorized environments.
</p>

<div class="highlight">
This Extension is designed exclusively for controlled examination environments and is intended for use only by authorized exam invigilators and institutional staff.
</div>

---

<h2>1. Purpose of the Extension</h2>
<p>
The SEB Config Verificator is developed to ensure the integrity and authenticity of Safe Exam Browser (SEB) configurations used during examinations.
</p>

<p>
Its primary goal is to:
</p>
<ul>
<li>Prevent tampering with SEB configuration files</li>
<li>Detect unauthorized modifications (e.g., enabling developer tools or bypass settings)</li>
<li>Ensure fair and secure examination conditions</li>
</ul>

---

<h2>2. Scope of Use</h2>
<ul>
<li>This Extension operates only on official institutional domains (e.g., *.iitp.ac.in)</li>
<li>It is not intended for public or general browsing usage</li>
<li>Access is limited to authorized personnel such as exam invigilators</li>
</ul>

<div class="warning">
Unauthorized use of this Extension outside institutional environments is not supported and may violate policies.
</div>

---

<h2>3. Information Accessed</h2>

<p>The Extension may access the following types of data:</p>

<h3>3.1 Session Data</h3>
<ul>
<li>Authentication session cookie (e.g., MoodleSession)</li>
<li>Used strictly to perform authenticated requests to the official exam server</li>
</ul>

<h3>3.2 Page Data</h3>
<ul>
<li>Current webpage URL</li>
<li>SEB configuration download links</li>
<li>SEB launch links (sebs:// protocol)</li>
</ul>

<h3>3.3 User-Provided Data</h3>
<ul>
<li>API keys entered by authorized users</li>
</ul>

---

<h2>4. How Information is Used</h2>

<p>All accessed data is used solely for:</p>

<ul>
<li>Validating that the SEB configuration loaded matches the official server version</li>
<li>Detecting inconsistencies between expected and actual configurations</li>
<li>Supporting real-time verification during examinations</li>
</ul>

<div class="highlight">
The Extension does NOT use data for tracking, analytics, advertising, or profiling purposes.
</div>

---

<h2>5. Data Transmission</h2>

<p>
To perform verification, certain data may be transmitted to a secure backend server operated for institutional purposes.
</p>

<ul>
<li>Session authentication may be temporarily used to fetch protected configuration data</li>
<li>Configuration data and metadata may be sent for validation</li>
<li>No persistent authentication data is retained</li>
</ul>

---

<h2>6. Data Storage Policy</h2>

<p>The Extension follows a strict no-storage policy:</p>

<ul>
<li>No session cookies are stored</li>
<li>No personal user data is stored</li>
<li>No browsing history is collected</li>
</ul>

<p>
All data processing occurs in real-time and is discarded immediately after verification.
</p>

---

<h2>7. Data Security</h2>

<p>
We implement appropriate technical measures to ensure:
</p>

<ul>
<li>Secure transmission of data</li>
<li>Protection against unauthorized access</li>
<li>Minimal data exposure</li>
</ul>

---

<h2>8. User Consent</h2>

<p>
Users are informed about data usage before using the Extension. By proceeding, users provide consent for:
</p>

<ul>
<li>Accessing required session and page data</li>
<li>Performing verification requests</li>
</ul>

---

<h2>9. Third-Party Sharing</h2>

<p>
We do NOT share data with third parties. All communication is restricted to:
</p>

<ul>
<li>Official institutional verification servers</li>
</ul>

---

<h2>10. Limitations</h2>

<p>
While the Extension enhances detection of tampering, it does not guarantee complete prevention of all forms of misuse. It is designed to work alongside:
</p>

<ul>
<li>Human supervision</li>
<li>Secure exam browser systems</li>
</ul>

---

<h2>11. Changes to This Policy</h2>

<p>
We may update this policy as needed. Updates will be reflected with a revised date.
</p>

